				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: HoH summon ~ How and where<a name="7596"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 26 03 5:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Been running around this area this last weekend and have been having some fun (bard style  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />) Anyhow Iv only found one decent place to kite in - didnt venture around in the back or near shrines as i would get random see invis mobs there. One thing I learned is this - furthest room back in FR (front right) is awesome ~ PERFECT for bards! Wat it is is a four spawn room - basically a square with little jut outs at mob spawn points. Mobs spawn in a smaller square within the room (not a square itself - mobs just spawn in a square pattern) Now the thing about this camp is no one else will kill here    A) because groups are almost non existant in HoH 
<br />
B) because other kiting classes kite in the either of the front two 6 spawn rooms 
<br />
C) because if u train - ur going to have about 15 adds on you before you make it out of the camp
<br />

<br />
The beauty of this camp is the mob respawn is about 20 minutes and each takes about 5 to 6 minutes to down (a min or so longer than the avg. razorfiend in PoV) Now there is a named that can spawn in here - dont remember name exactly but i was feeling balzy and started to kite him before others were down and BLAM 96 pct ~~ &quot;You have been summoned!&quot; &quot;Zoning, Please wait.&quot; Anyhow the trick with him is just dont kill him - kill everything else mez him and loot then keep him mezzed and camp out. If he isnt up just continue ur nice little pattern and ull have a constant flow of 2 mobs on you at a time. NOTE: I pulled by lulling back two mobs pulled front two and just ran about 2 tiles away from lulled ones until all were on me so i didnt get caught inbetween while pulling them all at once. 
<br />
Another NOTE: I have all my chants so i was doing max dmg from that angle and i have DotB so i was doing high end dmg from that angle. I didnt disc puretone at all so i expect if you were planning on kiting here for a good 4 hours (every 3 mobs is about a yellow AA) you could get in two puretones which would boost dotb just a bit unless u had something better. 
<br />

<br />
Anyhow usually even if there are groups here the will be glad to share because by the time they clear the 12 mob spawn before that room they start getting respawns. 
<br />

<br />
Anymore info be sure to share - and thanks!</span></td>
