			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: HoH summon ~ How and where<a name="7600"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 27 03 1:27 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There are roughly four very good spots to kite in Halls of Honor.  Three of these spots are the basements.  There are three basements in all, one in the northeast of the zone, one in the northwest, and one in the southeast.  Each basement has three rooms in it.  The first room is full of suits of armor, avoid these some can summon and see invis.  The second room is typically full of human guards (6 in total).  This room is very good for kiting and is the room Melodico was referring to I believe.  The third room is the &quot;trial&quot; room, which has a named mob that will con indifferent to you.  The mob will not attack you or assist any other mobs in the room, as such these rooms are also safe to kite in.  However, avoid the Northeast trial room because it has another named mob in it that will summon and kill you.
<br />

<br />
The fourth area that you can solo in is the south hero shrine.  It is divided into two rooms, each with three mobs in it.  You can kill all three easily before respawn.  The nice thing about the hero shrine is that two named can spawn in each room (the Valorian Guard in each room is the place holder) and each can drop spectral parchments (albeit rarely).  The named are level 66 suits of armor that don't cast or summon, as such they are very decent xp and easy kills.  
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps you out.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
