				<td colspan="2"><span>Sounds to me like you are doing NE basement from the assisting.summoning mob.  What I do is lull before I pull and then then kite in one of the corners of the room ( the side without the two mobs).  As long as you don't venture too far out into the center of the room you won't get any adds.  You can kill 3 easily before respawn and if you have IM 2/3 and DotB you can do 4 before respawn.  Of course if you don't care about a train behind you, you can always just kite everything at once and then use fading memories when you are done to clear agro if you have it.  The easiest basement by far to kite in is the NW basement in the back room though.  There are only two mobs in there, so you can kite those and then pull the two in from the other room with absolutely no chance of adds.  The hero shrine isn't bad either, you just have to be careful you don't accidently run into the wall and get stuck due to the rather tight area you are kiting in.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
